Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[416,596,748,775]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordobensis">
<emphasis box="[416,596,748,775]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. cordobensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="177" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 15 D–F) resemble those of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itacolomi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. itacolomi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[258,352,822,849]" captionStart="FIGURE 153" captionStartId="169.[136,235,1379,1403]" captionTargetBox="[161,1413,198,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-264@169.[151,1436,189,1355]" captionTargetPageId="169" captionText="FIGURE 153. Actinopus itacolomi sp. nov., male: A–C IBSP: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D UFMG 18876: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597563/files/figure.png" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Fig. 153</figureCitation>
A–C), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1842" box="[435,592,822,848]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipalpis">
<emphasis box="[435,592,822,848]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. longipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[608,703,822,849]" captionStart="FIGURE 156" captionStartId="172.[136,235,1679,1703]" captionTargetBox="[188,1382,198,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-114@172.[151,1435,189,1655]" captionTargetPageId="172" captionText="FIGURE 156. Actinopus longipalpis C. L. Koch, 1842, holotype, male: A–E ZMB 2107: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc- Prolateral Accessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel. D. Rastellum, dorsal; E. Rastellum, ventral. Scales lines: A–C: 1 mm; D–E: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597571/files/figure.png" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Fig. 156</figureCitation>
A–C), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[136,234,859,885]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ariasi">
<emphasis box="[136,234,859,885]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. ariasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[251,621,858,885]" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 12 D–F) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[183,280,895,922]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coylei">
<emphasis box="[183,280,895,922]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. coylei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[294,655,895,921]" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 16 D–F), by the PA continuous to PAc. They differ from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[168,299,968,995]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itacolomi">
<emphasis box="[168,299,968,995]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A itacolomi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1842" box="[314,472,968,995]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipalpis">
<emphasis box="[314,472,968,995]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. longipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[529,665,968,995]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pindapoy">
<emphasis box="[529,665,968,995]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. pindapoy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[682,778,968,995]" captionStart="FIGURE 159" captionStartId="176.[136,235,1273,1297]" captionTargetBox="[187,1358,189,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-264@176.[151,1436,186,1249]" captionTargetPageId="176" captionText="FIGURE 159. Actinopus pindapoy sp. nov., male: A–C ZMB 19824: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597577/files/figure.png" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">Fig. 159</figureCitation>
A–C) by the wider bulb and from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[640,739,1006,1032]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ariasi">
<emphasis box="[640,739,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. ariasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a conspicuous serrated area on embolar base and, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[398,773,1079,1105]" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[964,1061,158,185]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coylei">
<emphasis box="[964,1061,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="177" pageNumber="178">A. coylei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the legs with metatarsi and tarsi lighter (
<bibRefCitation author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[897,1260,195,221]" pageId="177" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 15 B).
</paragraph>
